<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-527-630  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 527 630.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  June 8 1990 n1442* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM launches LAN Server Version 1.2 for OS/2 Extended Edition inthe UK.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   LAN Server 1.2 (Computer network software) (product introduction)OS/2 Extended Edition 1.2 (Operating system) (usage).andO;Topic:     Local Area NetworksEnhancementsFile ServersFile Organization.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM LAUNCHES LAN SERVER 1.2 FOR OS/2andM;EXTENDED EDITION IN THE UKandM;IBM has announced that LAN Server Version 1.2 running under OS/2 ExtendedEdition Version 1.2 is now available in the UK.andP;  The company says that itoffers several significant enhancements over OS/2 LAN Server Version 1.0including the ability to support MS-DOS users more economically withoutlosing any MS-DOS function, since both MS-DOS LAN Requester and LAN SupportProgram are included in an OS/2 Version 1.2 server licence.andP;  For PS/2 users,IBM claims that the MS-DOS LAN Requester has more space in memory forapplications.andP;  Other options include the ability to run Version 1.2 on a4M-bit or 16M-bit Token-Ring local area network, IBM's PC Network, andEthernet DIS Version 2.2 or an IEEE 802.3 network.andP;  The number of filesavailable to a single server is said to be 30 times greater than before, andthe user profile management permits logon to both OS/2 Extended 1.2 and LANServer 1.2 through a single user identification or password.andP;  The filereplication system enables the administrator to replicate files from an OS/2server to another server or OS/2 requester on a time interval basis.andO;Application programming interface support has been extended to includeapplications for network messaging, shared resource management, and localarea network interprocess communications and security.andP;  OS/2 LAN ServerVersion 1.2 is available now and licences for #910.andP;  OS/2 LAN Server Version1.0 users may upgrade free of charge to Version 1.2 till August 20.andO;</TEXT></DOC>